4. Why This Hasn’t Happened Yet

Three main problems:

Launch Cost

Sending servers to orbit is expensive.

But reusable rockets (SpaceX, etc.) are lowering costs.

⸻

Radiation

Space radiation damages electronics.

Solutions include:
	•	hardened chips
	•	redundancy
	•	error correction

⸻

Maintenance

You can’t easily replace broken hardware.

So designs must be:
	•	modular
	•	robotic-serviceable
	•	highly redundant

⸻

